## 📋 Overview

**Feature:** AMS Findings Panel — Farmer Dashboard
**Round:** Round 1 — 2026
**Environment:** CENTEST
**Application:** Basic Income Support for Sustainability (BISS)
**Scope:** Pre-Submit only (Not Started or Draft)
**Test Type:** Test only (not regression)
**Created by:** Aniket Pathare | aniket.pathare@government.ie
**Date:** 28-Apr-2026
**Post-Submit Scenarios:** Separate ticket — BISSAGL-X

**Context:**
The AMS (Area Monitoring System) uses satellite imagery to monitor parcels declared under BISS.
When a potential non-compliance is found (e.g. Artificial Surface, crop mismatch, Agricultural
Activity), a Red finding is generated for that herd. These findings appear on the Farmer Dashboard
as an AMS Findings panel, prompting the farmer or agent to respond before 8 July 2026.

**Important — Date Message Changed from Last Year:**
The deadline message has been updated for 2026. All test cases must verify the panel shows
the new 2026 date and NOT the previous year’s deadline.

- Individual / Primary Partner: **“You have until 8 July 2026 to respond to your AMS notifications”**
- Non-Primary Partner: **“The Primary Partner has until 8 July 2026 to respond to your AMS notifications”**

